    <svcsection id="s16016" svcsectype="prodspec" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5227" date="03/31/1996">
        <title>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - 12/06/1994 and After</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>2000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>12/06/1994</startdate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>12/06/1994</startdate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>12/06/1994</startdate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>GENERAL</title>
                <lev1>
                    <specpara>
                        <important>
                            <para>Refer to GROUP 16 - AIR CONDITIONING BASIC THEORY, SYSTEM DIAGNOSIS AND SERVICE with
                                R-134a section in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for precautions and changes in
                                procedures and tools to use with R-134a refrigerant.
                            </para>
                        </important>
                    </specpara>
                    <para>The Blend-Air air conditioning and heating system is a combination unit (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601601">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Both the heater and air conditioner are housed in
                        one unit and use common ducts and blowers. The term "Blend-Air" refers to the mixing or blending
                        together of air from the cooling and heating systems. The unit provides for heating, cooling,
                        defrosting, dehumidification, and ventilation in any combination the driver chooses.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601601" figsize="pg-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601601" filename="../figg16/G1601601.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="514px" scalefitheight="392px"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. Blend-Air Air Conditioning and Heating System</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. HEATER CORE</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. BLEND-AIR DOOR LEVER</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. THERMOSTATIC SWITCH</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. THERMOSTATIC SWITCH CAPILLARY TUBE</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. LOW PRESSURE SWITCH</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. DRIP TRAY</callout1>
                            <callout1>7. EVAPORATOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>8. FILTER</callout1>
                            <callout1>9. BLOWER MOTOR SPEED CONTROL RESISTOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>10. BLOWER MOTOR VENT TUBE</callout1>
                            <callout1>11. BLOWER MOTOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>12. BLEND-AIR DOOR CONTROL CABLE</callout1>
                            <callout1>13. DEFROST DOOR CONTROL CABLE</callout1>
                            <callout1>14. BLEND-AIR DOOR CABLE TURNBUCKLE</callout1>
                            <callout1>15. DEFROST DOOR LEVER</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <para>The heater core, evaporator, blower motor, blower motor speed control resistor, filter,
                        thermostatic switch and low pressure switch are located in the unit and may be serviced without
                        removing the unit.
                    </para>
                    <para>The expansion valve and high pressure switch are located on the engine side of the dash
                        panel.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>This system does not have a hot water valve.</para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>COMPONENTS</title>
                    <para>For the description of air conditioning/heater system components, refer to
                        <emph type="bold">GROUP 16 - AIR CONDITIONING BASIC THEORY, SYSTEM DIAGNOSIS AND SERVICE with
                            R-134a section in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                        </emph>
                    </para>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
